						<summary>

						<p>Prākāra wall (in side) of the Narasiṁhasvāmi temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1764, Parābhava, Phālguṇa śu. 5, Wednesday.</hi> Irregular.</p>						

						<p>It records the construction of a <hi rend="italic">hōmaśāla</hi> and the kitchen-<hi rend="italic">maṇḍapa</hi> by Aragappa son of Jagamu-śeṭṭi and grandson of Raṁgiś-śeṭṭi, a devotee of Guru-Bhāskarāchārya and the recipient of boons from the goddess Vāsavāmba.</p>						

						</summary>
